1. Concentration based run¶

We first need to find emissions that ensure a constant atmospheric $CO_2$ concentration after the year of the pulse.

In [2]:
conc_in = return_empty_emissions(df_to_copy=False, start_year=1765, end_year=3100, timestep=1, scen_names=['yr_'+str(i) for i in range(1850,2006)], gases_in = ['carbon_dioxide'])
print(conc_in)
for label in ['yr_'+str(i) for i in range(1850,2020)]:
    t = int(label.split('yr_')[-1])

    conc_in.loc[:t,(label,'carbon_dioxide')]=ssp245.Concentrations.co2[ssp245.Concentrations.year<=t]
    conc_in.loc[t:,(label,'carbon_dioxide')]=ssp245.Concentrations.co2[ssp245.Concentrations.year==t][0]
print(conc_in)
test_gas = get_gas_parameter_defaults().reindex(conc_in.columns.levels[1],axis=1,level=1)

3. Read $CO_2$ data & Pulse run¶

Read the CO2 data first:

In [8]:
primap = pd.read_csv('../data/PRIMAP/Guetschow-et-al-2021-PRIMAP-hist_v2.3.1_20-Sep_2021.csv')
primap = primap.rename(columns={"category (IPCC2006_PRIMAP)": "category",
                                "area (ISO3)":"ISO3",
                                "scenario (PRIMAP-hist)":"scenario"})
#select the HISTCR scenario (country-reported data is prioritized over third-party data)
primap = primap[primap.scenario=='HISTCR']

# select National Total excluding LULUCF
primap = primap[primap.category=='M.0.EL']

co2_per_yr = primap[primap.entity=='CO2'].set_index('ISO3')

co2_per_yr = co2_per_yr.loc[:,[str(t) for t in range(1750,2020)]]
co2_per_yr.columns = co2_per_yr.columns.astype(int)
# convert Gg to Gt CO2
co2_per_yr = co2_per_yr/1e6

# convert Gt CO2 to Gt C !!!!
co2_per_yr = co2_per_yr/3.67

co2_per_yr.to_csv('../data/PRIMAP/primap_CO2.csv')
In [9]:

pulse_in = copy.deepcopy(control_in)

    pulse_in.loc[t,'yr_'+str(t)].carbon_dioxide = pulse_in.loc[t,'yr_'+str(t)].carbon_dioxide + co2_per_yr.loc['EARTH',t]

Calculation of IRF¶

In [18]:
irf_df = pd.DataFrame(index=range(1000))

for t in co2_per_yr.loc['EARTH',1850:2019].index:
    irf = co2_diff.loc[t:t+1000,'yr_'+str(t)]/(co2_per_yr.loc['EARTH',t]/2.123)
    irf.index = irf.index-t
    irf.iloc[0]=1
    irf = irf.rename(columns={'carbon_dioxide':t})
    irf_df = pd.concat((irf_df,irf),axis=1)

from matplotlib.ticker import (MultipleLocator, AutoMinorLocator)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(25, 15))
grid = plt.GridSpec(6, 10, hspace=3, wspace=0)
ax2 = plt.subplot(grid[:4, :])
ax1 = plt.subplot(grid[4:, :])

x = co2_per_yr.loc['EARTH'].index
y = co2_per_yr.loc['EARTH'].values
dydx = x  # first derivative
points = np.array([x, y]).T.reshape(-1, 1, 2)
segments = np.concatenate([points[:-1], points[1:]], axis=1)

# Create a continuous norm to map from data points to colors
norm = plt.Normalize(dydx.min(), dydx.max())
lc = LineCollection(segments, cmap='viridis', norm=norm)
# Set the values used for colormapping
lc.set_array(dydx)
line = ax1.add_collection(lc,'o')
ax1.set_xlim(1850,2019)
ax1.set_ylim(0,10)
ax1.set_xlabel('Year of emission pulse',size=25)
ax1.set_ylabel('Pulse (Gt C)',size=27,labelpad=15)
ax1.grid()



irf_df.plot.line(cmap=plt.cm.get_cmap('viridis'), figsize=(20,10), legend=False,grid=True,ax=ax2)

cbar = fig.colorbar(line, ax=[ax1,ax2],cmap=plt.cm.get_cmap('viridis'))
